							<hr width="100%" size="1" class="hrcolor" />
							<div class="post">The accelerometer is sensing the pull of gravity.&nbsp; If the accelerometer is flat the X and Y accelerations are 0 and the Z acceleration is -1g.&nbsp; As the accelerometer tilts the Z acceleration gets closer to 0 and the X and/or Y accelerations go up or down.&nbsp; Using some trig you can determine the pitch and roll angles.<br /><br />First thing to do is to calibrate the accelerometer so you can subtract the zero offset and calculate acceleration in g.</div>
