							<hr width="100%" size="1" class="hrcolor" />
							<div class="post">When you tilt the X axis up past 90 degrees, the Z axis goes through zero and then starts going positive.&nbsp; Since yrot is based on the X and Z measurements, when Z goes from negative to positive you get a different answer, even though Y is staying near zero.<br /><br />To get pitch and roll, try:<br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code:</div><div class="code">pitch=atan2(ax,sqrt((ay*ay)+(az*az)))<br />roll=atan2(ay,sqrt((ax*ax)+(az*az)))<br /></div><br />Note that the result is in Radians so if you want degrees you still have to convert.&nbsp; You shouldn&#039;t get a problem with both arguments to atan2() being zero unless your accelerometer is in free-fall. <img src="http://forum.arduino.cc/Smileys/arduinoWide/smiley.png" alt="smiley" border="0" /></div>
